A process where the normal flow of execution of prgm is interrupted is called as exception.
Exceptions can be handled but ERRORS can't be handled.

There are two types of exceptions,
- Checked  Exceptions(JVM) , ArrayIndexoutofbounds exception
- Unchecked Exceptions(JVM not aware of it), NullpointerException

There are 2 ways to handle exceptions.
- Try and Catch, Throws